WEBVTT

00:06.966 --> 00:09.009
Previously on
The Summer I Turned Pretty...

00:09.093 --> 00:11.011
I've decided to move ahead
with the sale.

00:11.095 --> 00:12.638
Actually, we're gonna have
an open house tomorrow.

00:12.722 --> 00:14.306
Surprise!

00:14.390 --> 00:16.183
We're losing the house.

00:16.267 --> 00:18.018
We'll figure it out together.

00:18.102 --> 00:19.770
You wrote a beautiful book.

00:19.854 --> 00:21.856
I think Susannah would want you
to share it with the world.

00:21.939 --> 00:24.358
Conrad may have listened to me
at one point,

00:24.442 --> 00:26.152
but I don't think he cares
what I think anymore.

00:26.235 --> 00:27.653
[Jeremiah] I'm glad
I don't have to do this alone.

00:27.737 --> 00:29.071
Yeah, I'm glad I came, too.

00:29.155 --> 00:31.532
♪ ♪

00:31.615 --> 00:33.284
[panting]

00:33.367 --> 00:35.077
Conrad, what's going on, man?

00:35.161 --> 00:37.163
- Conrad?
- [gasps loudly]

00:40.207 --> 00:42.209
♪ ♪

00:47.715 --> 00:51.260
[Conrad breathing heavily]

00:51.343 --> 00:53.304
[waves crashing]

00:53.387 --> 00:55.389
♪ ♪

00:58.225 --> 01:00.519
Conrad, man, what's going on?

01:02.396 --> 01:03.731
What happened?

01:04.774 --> 01:08.611
Panic attack.
I'm fine. I'll be fine.

01:10.571 --> 01:13.574
- I'm going to go get Jere.
- No. Don't get Jere.

01:15.034 --> 01:17.536
It's... I just need a second.

01:18.537 --> 01:19.997
Is there anything I can do?

01:20.080 --> 01:21.207
I don't know, man. Just talk.

01:21.289 --> 01:24.001
Okay? Just talk
about anything.

01:24.084 --> 01:27.338
Um, talk, right.
Um... Um...

01:30.132 --> 01:33.301
[stammers] The beach.

01:33.384 --> 01:35.304
The first time you guys
brought me here to surf,

01:35.387 --> 01:37.431
man, I was so freaked out.

01:37.515 --> 01:39.975
You and Jere had just
come back from some fancy

01:40.059 --> 01:43.187
surfing camp and you knew
all these cool tricks.

01:43.270 --> 01:46.607
I felt like such a little kid.
But you stayed and paddled

01:46.690 --> 01:48.776
with me till
we caught a wave together.

01:51.070 --> 01:52.988
I thought you were
the coolest person in the world.

01:53.072 --> 01:55.991
I guess you were
wrong about that one.

01:56.075 --> 01:57.076
No.

01:59.537 --> 02:01.372
You're still the coolest.

02:02.998 --> 02:04.625
You have these a lot?

02:08.044 --> 02:09.588
Yeah.

02:11.966 --> 02:14.343
More since my mom died.

02:23.978 --> 02:25.521
I'm glad you're here.

02:27.773 --> 02:29.900
So, you want to tell me
what got you all worked up?

02:29.984 --> 02:33.320
Or just be bros and
pretend this never happened?

02:35.739 --> 02:38.784
- Found out I got into Stanford.
- What? Are you serious?

02:38.868 --> 02:41.036
Yeah, man.
My mom had this fantasy about

02:41.120 --> 02:42.538
me finding myself
on the West Coast.

02:42.621 --> 02:44.123
Wait, wait, wait, Connie,
this is a good thing, man.

02:44.206 --> 02:45.916
No, you've been dreaming
about Stanford since you

02:46.000 --> 02:47.167
- were ten years old.
- Yeah, yeah, yeah.

02:47.251 --> 02:50.337
I know... but things
are just starting

02:50.421 --> 02:52.256
to get better with Jere,
and he's going

02:52.339 --> 02:53.716
to Finch in the fall,
which is close to Brown,

02:53.799 --> 02:55.216
so it just doesn't make sense

02:55.301 --> 02:56.719
- to transfer anymore...
- Hey, dude, dude, dude,

02:56.802 --> 02:59.930
you don't have to decide
this second or anything, okay?

03:02.099 --> 03:03.350
Just talk to Jere.

03:03.434 --> 03:05.519
He doesn't even know
I applied, man.

03:05.603 --> 03:07.813
So...

03:07.897 --> 03:10.149
Please don't tell him.

03:14.612 --> 03:16.488
I...

03:16.572 --> 03:19.199
I mean, Stanford's
not even an Ivy.

03:19.283 --> 03:21.243
So fuck 'em, right?

03:22.369 --> 03:23.871
Let's go.

03:28.751 --> 03:30.753
[birds chirping]

03:38.969 --> 03:40.304
[water running]

03:40.387 --> 03:41.639
[clears throat]

03:42.640 --> 03:44.224
♪ ♪

03:53.150 --> 03:55.277
- Mom?
- Yeah? Hi.

03:55.361 --> 03:57.947
- Oh.
- Oh. Damn. [laughs]

03:58.030 --> 03:59.990
[Skye] I know
we're not in California,

04:00.074 --> 04:02.076
- but save a little water.
- Thank you, honey.

04:03.827 --> 04:05.871
Oh. Hey, Belly.

04:05.955 --> 04:10.042
Hey. Sorry. I just, um,

04:10.125 --> 04:11.543
smelled muffins.

04:11.627 --> 04:13.671
- You want one?
- Yeah, sure.

04:13.754 --> 04:15.130
Uh, those are for
the open house.

04:15.214 --> 04:16.339
Morning.

04:16.423 --> 04:17.548
[door opens]

04:17.632 --> 04:19.510
Mmm, did somebody get muff...

04:19.593 --> 04:21.678
- muffins? Hi.
- Hey, Jeremiah.

04:21.762 --> 04:24.306
- Conrad.
- [Conrad] Skye.

04:24.390 --> 04:26.392
You didn't tell me
she was here, too.

04:26.475 --> 04:28.143
It's "they." Not "she."

04:28.227 --> 04:31.730
God, I guess it's been like
a decade since I saw you guys.

04:31.814 --> 04:34.650
Um, how are you doing
since your mom?

04:35.651 --> 04:37.861
- It's been rough.
- Rougher now

04:37.945 --> 04:39.363
that our aunt's
stealing our house.

04:39.446 --> 04:41.949
I'm not stealing
anything, Conrad.

04:42.032 --> 04:43.742
Like it or not,
I get to choose what happens

04:43.826 --> 04:46.286
to this house and I choose
to put it on the market.

04:48.247 --> 04:53.293
You boys should get on the road.
Beat the traffic back to Boston.

04:53.377 --> 04:55.254
There's no chance. We're
staying for the open house.

04:55.337 --> 04:59.216
Uh, no, no, no. I can't
have a bunch of teenagers

04:59.299 --> 05:01.635
chasing everybody away.
Call your father,

05:01.719 --> 05:04.054
because this isn't
an Aunt Julia problem.

05:04.138 --> 05:06.140
Except it is.

05:06.223 --> 05:08.100
Because you are the problem.

05:09.601 --> 05:11.103
I don't have time for this.

05:14.189 --> 05:16.692
Conrad, she's still your family.

05:16.775 --> 05:18.277
Then why is she
doing this to us?

05:18.360 --> 05:19.778
- This is hard for her, too.
- [Conrad] Really?

05:19.862 --> 05:22.573
Seems like she's doing this
all pretty fucking easily.

05:27.161 --> 05:29.538
He's grown into
quite the asshole.

05:31.290 --> 05:32.707
You have no idea.

05:38.630 --> 05:40.883
This is your room, I take it?

05:43.010 --> 05:45.554
- Not for long, apparently.
- [scoffs]

05:45.637 --> 05:49.892
It used to be mine, actually.
It was different back then.

05:49.975 --> 05:52.436
More rustic.

05:52.519 --> 05:54.354
But this is nice.

05:54.438 --> 05:59.318
It's, um, warm.
Your mother's touch.

06:00.944 --> 06:03.238
Keep the house in
the family and it's yours.

06:03.322 --> 06:04.823
How generous of you.

06:04.907 --> 06:07.534
I know my mom's gone,
but here she's not.

06:07.618 --> 06:09.578
She picked out everything
in this house.

06:09.661 --> 06:11.789
She planted every flower
in the garden.

06:13.165 --> 06:14.541
This was her favorite place
in the world.

06:14.625 --> 06:16.668
I understand that your family

06:16.752 --> 06:20.214
has wonderful memories here,
and you will always have them.

06:21.298 --> 06:22.758
Memories are like that.

06:23.759 --> 06:26.178
It is not the same,
and you know that.

06:26.261 --> 06:28.472
This house is on
the other side of the country

06:28.555 --> 06:29.848
from where I live.

06:29.932 --> 06:31.767
It'd cost tens of thousands
of dollars

06:31.850 --> 06:34.019
to maintain a year.
Money that I don't have.

06:34.103 --> 06:35.646
[loud clang echoes]

06:35.729 --> 06:37.523
What-what was that?

06:39.191 --> 06:41.985
Sounded like
an Aunt Julia problem to me.

06:43.028 --> 06:44.154
[scoffs]

06:45.280 --> 06:47.407
How many people are
in this house?

06:47.491 --> 06:49.493
Yeah, I remembered to lock
the door last night.

06:49.576 --> 06:50.744
I'm not a child.

06:50.828 --> 06:52.830
What are you wearing right now?

06:52.913 --> 06:54.540
Okay, I forgot mine. Okay?

06:54.623 --> 06:56.707
And these are the only ones
left in the drawer.

06:56.792 --> 06:58.544
And they're fucking
comfortable. Okay?

06:58.627 --> 06:59.586
Why are you
whispering right now?

06:59.670 --> 07:01.088
- 'Cause Laurel.
- Is that Taylor?

07:01.171 --> 07:03.048
[Steven] Uh, yes,

07:03.132 --> 07:05.384
it is Taylor.
Belly must have brought her over

07:05.467 --> 07:07.219
for a change of scenery.
I mean,

07:07.302 --> 07:08.512
between you and me,
she doesn't look too good.

07:08.595 --> 07:10.097
You know? I mean, I don't
even think she's showered

07:10.180 --> 07:11.390
since the breakup.

07:11.473 --> 07:13.183
[Laurel] Okay, well,

07:13.267 --> 07:14.893
keep an eye on everything
and don't let the girls

07:14.977 --> 07:16.145
- eat snacks in my bed.
- Yeah.

07:16.228 --> 07:18.230
Yeah, okay. A-And remember,

07:18.313 --> 07:20.065
you're going to kill it.
You're my favorite author.

07:20.149 --> 07:21.733
Brandon Sanderson is
your favorite author.

07:21.817 --> 07:23.193
And he's here, by the way.

07:23.277 --> 07:24.778
Can you please get
a signed copy of his new book?

07:24.862 --> 07:26.530
Love you. Thank you. Bye!

07:26.613 --> 07:30.325
You're a terrible liar.
And I never smell bad.

07:31.368 --> 07:33.370
[knocking]

07:33.453 --> 07:34.496
[door opens]

07:34.580 --> 07:36.165
[Taylor] Ooh, give me some.

07:37.791 --> 07:39.376
Bigger than that.

07:39.459 --> 07:42.754
So, why are you hiding up here?

07:42.838 --> 07:45.883
Are you avoiding that aunt
or Conrad?

07:45.966 --> 07:48.802
Taylor, I'm just
eating breakfast.

07:48.886 --> 07:50.137
Maybe a little bit of both?

07:50.220 --> 07:51.889
I honestly have no idea.

07:51.972 --> 07:54.266
I know that you came here
with the best intentions,

07:54.349 --> 07:57.311
but this is, like,
their family drama.

07:57.394 --> 07:59.104
I just don't want you to
get sucked back into it.

07:59.188 --> 08:00.772
I'm not going to get
sucked back into it.

08:00.856 --> 08:04.651
But I know that if the open
house happens today and someone

08:04.735 --> 08:06.612
makes Aunt Julia an offer,
then it's game over.

08:06.695 --> 08:08.113
- Well, I know, but...
- And I just, I don't understand

08:08.197 --> 08:10.324
why she's in such a rush
to sell.

08:10.407 --> 08:12.034
I don't know, Belly. I mean,

08:12.117 --> 08:14.161
I'm sure that
she has her reasons.

08:16.747 --> 08:18.916
Let's go do some drills
down by the beach.

08:18.999 --> 08:20.667
Volleyball camp starts
in like five days.

08:20.751 --> 08:23.086
I haven't touched
a volleyball in months.

08:23.170 --> 08:24.880
I can forget about
getting my captaincy back.

08:24.963 --> 08:26.590
I'll be lucky if
I even make the team.

08:26.673 --> 08:29.635
Look, did blowing it
at regionals

08:29.718 --> 08:32.763
crush your confidence?
Clearly.

08:32.846 --> 08:35.432
Are you Coach's favorite
player right now? Hell no.

08:35.515 --> 08:37.934
Have you gotten incredibly rusty
in the offseason?

08:38.018 --> 08:39.227
Like, without a doubt.

08:39.311 --> 08:40.938
Am I helping

08:41.020 --> 08:43.315
by acknowledging
your worst fears?

08:43.398 --> 08:45.067
Probably not.

08:45.150 --> 08:47.736
Okay, look,
all I'm trying to say

08:47.819 --> 08:50.030
is that the past
doesn't determine your fate.

08:50.113 --> 08:52.157
It's-it's the choices
that you make today.

08:52.241 --> 08:54.618
Trust me, I know things.

08:56.286 --> 08:59.414
Um, are there more
of these downstairs?

08:59.498 --> 09:01.583
[laughs] It was hard enough
for me to get this one.

09:01.667 --> 09:04.628
[both laughing]

09:04.711 --> 09:06.338
[doorbell rings]

09:08.590 --> 09:09.883
Hi. Can I help you?

09:09.967 --> 09:12.219
Sandy Denati.
I'm looking for Julia.

09:12.302 --> 09:14.221
Right. Yes, uh,
for the open house.

09:15.639 --> 09:18.100
You know, Julia actually
decided to cancel.

09:18.183 --> 09:19.559
Yeah, it's last-minute,

09:19.643 --> 09:22.229
but, um, she's having
some second thoughts.

09:22.312 --> 09:23.689
Sorry, who are you?

09:23.772 --> 09:27.150
She's my girlfriend, and she's,
um, and she's right.

09:27.234 --> 09:29.528
The house is not for sale.

09:29.611 --> 09:32.155
Conrad Fisher, right?

09:32.239 --> 09:34.032
It's nice to see you.
I am sorry about your mom.

09:34.116 --> 09:35.784
Well, clearly
not sorry enough to pass up

09:35.867 --> 09:36.952
the opportunity
to sell her house.

09:37.035 --> 09:38.996
I'm just doing my job.

09:39.079 --> 09:40.497
Well, consider this
an unexpected day off.

09:40.580 --> 09:42.207
[Julia] Ignore them.
Ignore them.

09:42.290 --> 09:44.626
There will be
an open house today.

09:44.710 --> 09:47.296
But there does seem
to be a minor

09:47.379 --> 09:50.132
problem with the AC. It died.

09:50.215 --> 09:52.342
That is not
a minor problem, Julia.

09:52.426 --> 09:54.553
It is supposed to hit 95 today.

09:54.636 --> 09:57.222
Yeah. Okay, um,
let's chat outside for a minute.

10:03.145 --> 10:06.231
I'm sorry. I didn't mean
to call you my girlfriend.

10:07.858 --> 10:09.484
Don't worry about it.
It's cool.

10:14.990 --> 10:16.116
Hey, is everything okay?

10:16.199 --> 10:18.994
- No, the realtor just got here.
- Shit.

10:19.077 --> 10:21.038
- What are we going to do?
- I don't know what else
we can do.

10:21.121 --> 10:24.458
Well, maybe Skye has some
information that could help us.

10:24.541 --> 10:26.668
I don't know. If only we could
get a moment alone with her.

10:26.752 --> 10:29.212
- Them.
- Right. Thanks.

10:29.296 --> 10:31.798
Well, good luck because
those two are inseparable.

10:33.884 --> 10:35.302
I don't fucking know.

10:43.977 --> 10:46.855
It's so hot.
It's like 2,000 degrees in here.

10:46.938 --> 10:49.024
Aunt Julia said the AC
is broken.

10:49.107 --> 10:50.567
Oh, what? No way.

10:50.650 --> 10:53.528
Today's open house
has been canceled.

10:53.612 --> 10:55.864
So I need you all
out of the house while

10:55.947 --> 10:58.784
I get the AC guy here
to do some work.

10:58.867 --> 11:01.328
Also, uh, who is the AC guy?

11:01.411 --> 11:02.788
[Skye] Uh, do you want me
to look one up for you?

11:02.871 --> 11:03.955
Uh, no, no, that's okay.

11:04.039 --> 11:06.666
I'm certain Susannah has
her preferred technician

11:06.750 --> 11:09.378
and four approved backups
right here.

11:09.461 --> 11:11.880
Great. Now we don't have to
lie about the black mold

11:11.963 --> 11:13.382
to the buyers.
Let's go to the beach.

11:13.465 --> 11:14.925
- I'm not leaving.
- [Jeremiah] Come on, Conrad.

11:15.008 --> 11:17.010
We've won this round.
Let's just get out of here.

11:17.094 --> 11:19.096
- The mall has good AC.
- [Conrad] Cool. Have fun.

11:19.179 --> 11:20.263
I didn't ditch finals

11:20.347 --> 11:22.140
just to leave this house
for the taking by...

11:22.224 --> 11:24.893
Conrad, I'm trying... straining
to keep my shit together.

11:24.976 --> 11:26.520
You've already ruined my day.

11:26.603 --> 11:29.106
The least you could do is get
out of my hair for a few hours.

11:29.189 --> 11:30.565
- You think
you're the only one...
- What about the boardwalk?

11:30.649 --> 11:32.526
Yeah, the boardwalk.
That's a great idea.

11:32.609 --> 11:35.028
- [Steven] Yeah, I'm down.
- [Taylor] Yeah, me too.

11:35.112 --> 11:36.863
[Conrad] Yeah, fine. Yeah.

11:36.947 --> 11:38.365
Hey, you should
come with us, Skye.

11:38.448 --> 11:42.828
Oh, um, sounds very state fair.

11:42.911 --> 11:45.414
I think I should
just stay with you, right?

11:45.497 --> 11:47.915
No. Wasn't my favorite,
but you might like it.

11:47.999 --> 11:49.543
I shouldn't just stay with you?

11:49.626 --> 11:53.171
No, I'll be fine.
After this, I'm going to

11:53.255 --> 11:56.258
go back to the hotel
for a nap and a NAN fan.

11:57.676 --> 11:58.927
Guess I'm coming with you guys.

11:59.010 --> 12:00.220
- [Belly] Okay.
- [Taylor] Great!

12:00.303 --> 12:01.430
- Let's go.
- [Skye] Whoo!

12:01.513 --> 12:02.639
- Cousins to Cousins.
- [Taylor] Let's go.

12:02.722 --> 12:04.099
- [Steven] Yeah.
- [Jeremiah] Let's roll.

12:04.182 --> 12:07.060
- [indistinct chatter]
- [door opens]

12:07.144 --> 12:09.187
Hey, Jere,
can you just hold on a sec?

12:09.271 --> 12:10.647
I want to talk to you
about something.

12:10.730 --> 12:12.065
Yeah, sure, sure. What?

12:12.149 --> 12:15.402
I hope you're not mad
that I invited Skye.

12:15.485 --> 12:17.696
I know things are weird
with their mom.

12:17.779 --> 12:19.948
Oh, no, it was nice of you.

12:20.031 --> 12:22.409
Yeah, I just, I think that,
you know, once they get

12:22.492 --> 12:24.995
to see more of Cousins
and hang out with you guys,

12:25.078 --> 12:28.123
then they'll see why
we love this place so much.

12:28.206 --> 12:30.625
And, I mean, I just know
they'll be on our side.

12:32.586 --> 12:34.713
Like it. I'll follow your lead.

12:34.796 --> 12:36.423
Okay. Thanks. Yeah.

12:36.506 --> 12:40.051
It's actually kind of nice
to hang out with Skye.

12:40.135 --> 12:44.848
You know, it's just me,
my dad and Conrad now,

12:44.931 --> 12:46.808
so it's nice
to feel like our family

12:46.892 --> 12:48.477
is a little bit bigger
than that.

12:48.560 --> 12:50.854
Well, we're your family, too.

12:54.733 --> 12:58.236
Hey, thanks for
everything that you're doing.

12:59.488 --> 13:01.281
It means a lot.

13:01.364 --> 13:03.617
[laughs softly] Let's go.

13:03.700 --> 13:05.535
[♪ Bleachers:
"Don't Take the Money"]

13:05.619 --> 13:08.747
♪ I'm in love
and you've got me, runaway ♪

13:08.830 --> 13:11.541
♪ You steal the air
out of my lungs ♪

13:11.625 --> 13:13.752
♪ You make me feel it ♪

13:13.835 --> 13:17.881
♪ I pray for everything we lost,
buy back the secrets ♪

13:17.964 --> 13:19.466
♪ Your hand forever's
all I want ♪

13:19.549 --> 13:22.385
♪ Don't take the money ♪

13:22.469 --> 13:24.888
♪ Don't take the money ♪♪

13:28.642 --> 13:30.143
See, aren't you glad we came?

13:30.227 --> 13:32.938
How is this any less hot
than it would be inside?

13:33.021 --> 13:36.775
Because you have the magical
sea breeze to cool you down.

13:36.858 --> 13:38.109
Cool breeze, my ass.

13:38.193 --> 13:42.113
I want some ice cream.
Nature's air conditioning.

13:44.282 --> 13:46.660
You know, I'm kind of
a natural introvert,

13:46.743 --> 13:48.954
so I can't tell if
this place is horrifying

13:49.037 --> 13:51.498
or if it's just, like,
my lizard brain in action.

13:51.581 --> 13:53.792
- It's fun, I promise.
- Fun?

13:53.875 --> 13:55.669
Because I seem to
remember the last time

13:55.752 --> 13:58.255
we were here, you were crying.

13:58.338 --> 14:01.299
Belly was 12. And Conrad
beat her at Shoot Your Shot.

14:01.383 --> 14:04.094
And her penalty was to
ride the Tower of Terror.

14:04.177 --> 14:05.887
- Yep.
- Belly, you were so scared,

14:05.971 --> 14:07.138
you threw up.

14:07.222 --> 14:09.808
- I was sick.
- Sick with fear.

14:09.891 --> 14:11.768
My mom had to
throw out your clothes

14:11.851 --> 14:13.395
and carry you home in a caftan.

14:13.478 --> 14:15.063
- I know.
- [laughter]

