25:50.549 --> 25:52.510
- to see her.
- [♪ Taylor Swift:
"Sweet Nothing"]

25:52.593 --> 25:54.095
♪ They said the end is coming ♪

25:54.178 --> 25:56.055
♪ Everyone's up to something ♪

25:56.138 --> 26:01.018
♪ I find myself running
home to your sweet nothings...

26:01.102 --> 26:02.895
Okay, come with me.

26:02.979 --> 26:06.023
♪ You're in the kitchen humming,
all that you ever wanted ♪

26:06.107 --> 26:09.443
♪ From me was sweet nothing ♪

26:09.527 --> 26:12.029
- How many rings?
- We'll take three.

26:12.113 --> 26:14.115
- I like your shorts.
- Thanks.

26:14.198 --> 26:15.658
Yeah, they're really nice.

26:15.741 --> 26:17.410
I thought you said
they were too short

26:17.493 --> 26:19.996
when I wore the exact same ones
two days ago.

26:20.079 --> 26:22.498
Do you think they're too short?

26:24.500 --> 26:26.502
All right, Con,
I'm gonna go get a lemonade.

26:26.585 --> 26:28.170
So, win me a prize, okay?

26:28.254 --> 26:30.006
♪ Everyone's up to something ♪

26:30.089 --> 26:34.927
♪ I find myself running
home to your sweet nothings ♪

26:35.011 --> 26:36.887
♪ Outside, they're push
and shoving ♪

26:36.971 --> 26:38.723
♪ You're in
the kitchen humming ♪

26:38.806 --> 26:43.269
♪ All that you ever wanted
from me was sweet nothing ♪

26:43.352 --> 26:45.438
♪ They said the end is coming ♪

26:45.521 --> 26:47.273
♪ Everyone's up to something ♪

26:47.356 --> 26:52.320
♪ All that you ever wanted
from me was sweet nothing ♪

26:54.196 --> 26:55.865
How come you never came back?

26:55.948 --> 26:57.575
The line for the...

26:57.658 --> 27:00.870
the Ferris wheel
was really long.

27:00.953 --> 27:03.164
♪ On the way home...

27:03.247 --> 27:05.207
Angie said this is
the best prize they have.

27:05.291 --> 27:07.376
I thought you might like it.

27:07.460 --> 27:09.295
♪ This happens all the time...

27:09.378 --> 27:12.923
I'd rather have had the giraffe,
but thanks.

27:13.007 --> 27:16.135
The worst part is,
he was trying to be nice.

27:16.218 --> 27:19.096
He didn't know
my heart was breaking.

27:19.180 --> 27:21.057
[Conrad] Oh, wow.

27:21.140 --> 27:24.018
They haven't changed
these prizes in years.

27:24.101 --> 27:25.186
[chuckles softly]

27:25.269 --> 27:26.729
You can get Junior Mint
a friend.

27:26.812 --> 27:27.813
[Belly] Yeah.

27:27.897 --> 27:29.565
[chuckles softly]

27:31.192 --> 27:32.985
You know what?
I'll take the giraffe.

27:33.069 --> 27:35.654
Thank you. [chuckles]

27:35.738 --> 27:37.073
All right!

27:37.156 --> 27:39.075
So we finally get to pick,

27:39.158 --> 27:41.410
and I choose dancing.

27:41.494 --> 27:43.704
- Okay!
- [exclaiming]

27:45.956 --> 27:47.625
I'm just... I'm just gonna say

27:47.708 --> 27:50.044
it was supremely satisfying

27:50.127 --> 27:51.796
watching you wipe the floor
with Conrad

27:51.879 --> 27:53.297
after everything
he put you through.

27:53.381 --> 27:54.757
- It was like...
- Taylor, come on.

27:54.840 --> 27:56.801
I mean, he and I are fine.

27:56.884 --> 27:58.344
It was fun, even.

27:58.427 --> 28:01.764
Really? You guys can just, like,
have fun together casually now?

28:01.847 --> 28:03.015
- Yeah, I guess.
- Really?

28:03.099 --> 28:04.475
- Yeah.
- That's...

28:04.558 --> 28:06.102
kind of major.

28:06.185 --> 28:07.436
[laughs]

28:07.520 --> 28:08.604
Hey, uh, Steven.

28:08.687 --> 28:09.897
Yeah.

28:10.898 --> 28:13.567
Isn't it, um,
just such a coincidence

28:13.651 --> 28:16.487
that, uh, the AC broke
during a heat wave

28:16.570 --> 28:19.156
right after the future
engineering student arrived?

28:19.240 --> 28:21.367
[chuckles] I have no idea
what you're talking about.

28:21.450 --> 28:23.119
- Really?
- Mm-hmm.

28:23.202 --> 28:25.538
I love a happy accident.

28:26.539 --> 28:28.457
Hey, Belly. Belly.

28:28.541 --> 28:29.667
Ready?

28:29.750 --> 28:31.252
- [giggles]
- [laughs]

28:31.335 --> 28:33.796
- [laughing]
- Are you gonna keep just,
like...

28:33.879 --> 28:35.214
Are you gonna be doing that
all day?

28:35.297 --> 28:37.133
Is that gonna be, like,
your thing today?

28:37.216 --> 28:39.552
Eh. [chuckles]
Uh, maybe. I don't know.

28:39.635 --> 28:40.928
- Okay.
- [sniffs] Oh, wait.

28:41.011 --> 28:41.971
[clears throat]

28:42.054 --> 28:43.222
Do you smell that?

28:43.305 --> 28:45.891
- What?
- I think I smell, uh...

28:45.975 --> 28:47.309
a comeback.

28:47.393 --> 28:49.270
- Oh, do you? Okay, yeah.
- [laughs] Oh, yeah. I do.

28:49.353 --> 28:50.604
- [chuckles]
- You sure about that?

28:50.688 --> 28:52.440
'Cause if you're sure, I mean,

28:52.523 --> 28:54.942
I'd be willing
to make a little side bet.

28:55.025 --> 28:57.153
All right. Keep talking.

28:57.236 --> 28:59.905
I was just thinking,
if you wanted, um...

28:59.989 --> 29:03.742
maybe whichever one of us loses
has to ride the Tower of Terror.

29:03.826 --> 29:05.369
[chuckles]

29:05.453 --> 29:08.289
You used to cry every time you
looked at the Tower of Terror.

29:08.372 --> 29:10.207
- I... I...
- Yeah. [stammers]

29:10.291 --> 29:13.210
I'm very excited
to see it happen again.

29:13.294 --> 29:14.211
- Okay.
- Mm-hmm.

29:14.295 --> 29:15.754
- You're on then.
- Mm-hmm.

29:15.838 --> 29:18.466
He made it so hard
not to love him.

29:18.549 --> 29:21.260
When he was sweet like this,
I remembered why I did.

29:21.343 --> 29:23.554
Used to love him, I mean.

29:24.930 --> 29:26.932
♪ ♪

29:32.104 --> 29:33.981
Did I hear you talking
about the Tower of Terror?

29:34.064 --> 29:35.274
Because I'm pretty sure

29:35.357 --> 29:37.193
that's only gonna end
with one of you in tears.

29:37.276 --> 29:39.778
- Yeah, well, better him
than me, right? [chuckles]
- Agreed.

29:39.862 --> 29:41.405
And, I mean, at least
he'll be in a good mood,

29:41.489 --> 29:44.492
uh, right up until he sheds
his first tear.

29:44.575 --> 29:45.826
[chuckles softly]

29:45.910 --> 29:47.703
You know, competition is the key
to making Conrad happy.

29:47.786 --> 29:50.998
I mean,
I know you both very well.

29:51.081 --> 29:52.625
Oh, yeah?

29:52.708 --> 29:55.127
Well, what's the key
to making me happy, Belly?

29:55.211 --> 29:56.378
[chuckles]

29:56.462 --> 29:57.713
Um...

29:57.796 --> 29:59.048
Cheeseburgers.

29:59.131 --> 30:00.716
Correct.

30:00.799 --> 30:02.051
Ariana Grande.

30:02.134 --> 30:03.636
Always.

30:03.719 --> 30:05.137
Uh...

30:05.221 --> 30:06.347
[chuckles]

30:06.430 --> 30:08.682
And correcting
people who say "bru-shetta."

30:08.766 --> 30:10.267
[laughs]

30:10.351 --> 30:12.394
- 'Cause it's "bru-sketta."
- Yeah.

30:12.478 --> 30:14.980
- [giggles]
- Damn, you're good, Belly.

30:15.064 --> 30:16.524
What can I say?

30:16.607 --> 30:18.317
- Good luck.
- Jere.

30:18.400 --> 30:20.110
- Ready? Yeah?
- My moves...

30:20.194 --> 30:21.362
are legendary.

30:21.445 --> 30:22.696
- Yeah.
- Oh, I know.
- I got this.

30:22.780 --> 30:24.114
Skye's up.

30:24.198 --> 30:26.367
- Oh.
- Really not a great idea

30:26.450 --> 30:27.868
- if we want to win.
- You'll be great at it.

30:27.952 --> 30:30.704
It's basically just math
with your feet.

30:31.956 --> 30:34.083
They'll never see you coming.
This is how we win.

30:34.166 --> 30:35.334
All right?

30:35.417 --> 30:37.461
- You got it.
- Bring it on, cuz.

30:37.545 --> 30:39.922
You know, Skye, I feel like
we've gotten closer today.

30:40.005 --> 30:42.049
It would be a shame
if my dance moves

30:42.132 --> 30:43.592
were to affect our relationship.

30:44.635 --> 30:45.719
We'll see.

30:45.803 --> 30:47.680
- All right.
- Let's go, Skye.

30:47.763 --> 30:50.307
- [Conrad] Come on, Jere.
- All right. Game on.
- Come on, Skye!

30:50.391 --> 30:52.184
- All right. Whoo! You got it!
- [Conrad/Cam] Come on, Jere.

30:52.268 --> 30:54.186
[♪ Ariana Grande:
"Side to Side"]

30:54.270 --> 30:55.896
- Come on.
- I got this.

30:55.980 --> 30:59.817
- Keep it up, keep it up.
- [Jeremiah] I got it.

30:59.900 --> 31:02.570
- ♪ Say I should give you up ♪
- [overlapping chatter]

31:02.653 --> 31:04.530
- That's all you got, Jere?
Come on.
- Oh, yeah?

31:04.613 --> 31:07.783
- ♪ 'Cause I ♪
- What?

31:07.866 --> 31:09.410
♪ I've been here all night ♪

31:09.493 --> 31:12.288
[laughs] I think Skye might
actually be good at this.

31:12.371 --> 31:14.164
[Belly] I mean, I was just
making the math thing up,

31:14.248 --> 31:15.541
but I think you're right.
[laughs]

31:15.624 --> 31:18.002
Fuck me. You're incredible.

31:18.085 --> 31:19.420
Go, Skye!

31:19.503 --> 31:20.629
- Jeremiah, come on!
- I'm trying!

31:20.713 --> 31:22.756
♪ ♪

31:22.840 --> 31:25.426
[game announcer] Perfect!
Perfect! Fantastic!

31:25.509 --> 31:27.177
Ah!

31:27.261 --> 31:28.387
- [groaning]
- I'm tired!

31:28.470 --> 31:30.431
♪ ♪

31:30.514 --> 31:31.432
Get her!

31:31.515 --> 31:32.933
- Just step it up!
- Go, Skye!

31:33.017 --> 31:34.059
- [laughing]
- [Steven] Get her, dude.

31:34.143 --> 31:37.563
♪ ♪

31:37.646 --> 31:38.564
[song ends]

31:38.647 --> 31:40.899
- Oh, my God!
- [cheering]

31:40.983 --> 31:42.359
- Yeah!
- Ooh! I don't do hugs.

31:42.443 --> 31:43.694
- I don't do hugs.
- What?

31:43.777 --> 31:45.362
- Really?
- Okay. Like, all right.

31:45.446 --> 31:46.697
Where next?

31:46.780 --> 31:48.198
Follow me.

31:48.282 --> 31:49.825
- Let's go.
- I'm baffled right now.

31:49.908 --> 31:51.702
Really? Those are...
those are your legendary moves?

31:51.785 --> 31:52.870
Oh, okay.
Like you could do better?

31:52.953 --> 31:54.747
- [indistinct chatter]
- That's his life story!

31:54.830 --> 31:57.333
[laughter, chatter continue]

31:57.416 --> 31:59.209
[Jeremiah] Watch it.

32:00.961 --> 32:03.714
[Susannah] Guys,
let's take a picture.

32:03.797 --> 32:05.799
- [laughter]
- [Laurel] Okay.

32:05.883 --> 32:06.800
[chuckling]

32:06.884 --> 32:08.886
I'm doing it.

32:08.969 --> 32:12.181
[woman] One, two, three.
Say cheese.

32:12.264 --> 32:14.516
[all] Cheese!

32:14.600 --> 32:16.602
♪ ♪

32:27.571 --> 32:29.490
- [message sends]
- [Laurel] You see,

32:29.573 --> 32:32.660
it's not really a book
about grief at all.

32:32.743 --> 32:35.120
It's a book about... friendship.

32:35.204 --> 32:36.288
Love.

32:36.372 --> 32:37.539
Huh.

32:44.546 --> 32:46.965
Well, this is
all very impressive.

32:47.049 --> 32:48.092
[chuckles]

32:48.175 --> 32:49.468
Cleveland!

32:49.551 --> 32:51.595
You look like you're having fun.

32:51.679 --> 32:52.930
[groans, sighs]

32:53.013 --> 32:54.682
I really hope there's wine
in those coffee cups.

32:54.765 --> 32:57.518
I mean, there can be.

32:57.601 --> 32:58.977
- [snorts]
- [laughs]

32:59.061 --> 33:00.229
So, uh...

33:00.312 --> 33:03.190
how's the life
of a saleswoman treating you?

33:03.273 --> 33:04.858
Oh, you know,
it's soul-destroying,

33:04.942 --> 33:06.860
deeply traumatic, making me
question every decision

33:06.944 --> 33:08.487
in my life
I've made up to this point.

33:08.570 --> 33:10.906
Sounds great, you know?

33:10.989 --> 33:12.741
Nonstop bliss.

33:14.702 --> 33:17.079
- So you're totally fine.
- [chuckles]

33:17.162 --> 33:18.288
I, um...

33:18.372 --> 33:20.541
reached out to Conrad
before the funeral,

33:20.624 --> 33:22.960
but that boy isn't always easy
to get ahold of.

33:23.043 --> 33:24.503
It's hard for him.

33:24.586 --> 33:26.171
For all of them.

33:28.465 --> 33:30.968
It's okay for it
to be hard for you, too.

33:32.177 --> 33:33.679
[chuckles softly]

33:33.762 --> 33:35.305
Fine.

33:35.389 --> 33:37.224
It's been hard.

33:38.350 --> 33:40.185
Well, you look great.

33:40.269 --> 33:42.771
[chuckles] Well,
looks can be deceiving.

33:44.565 --> 33:47.735
Look, things may have fizzled
between us, but...

33:47.818 --> 33:49.653
you can always talk to me.

33:51.780 --> 33:53.532
We had so long
to prepare for this,

33:53.615 --> 33:55.951
and I still have no fucking idea
how to process it,

33:56.034 --> 33:57.953
let alone talk about it.

33:59.455 --> 34:01.540
Belly isn't handling it well.

34:02.666 --> 34:03.959
I don't know how to help her.

34:04.042 --> 34:06.253
Well, maybe you don't need
to help her.

34:07.337 --> 34:09.255
- You're clearly not a parent.
- [scoffs]

34:09.339 --> 34:11.759
Look, something
really shitty happened,

34:11.842 --> 34:14.011
and you can't fix it. But...

34:14.094 --> 34:16.638
you can let her know
that you're feeling it, too.

34:16.722 --> 34:20.893
She may just need to know that
she's not alone in her feelings.

34:20.976 --> 34:23.061
I hear you, but...

34:23.145 --> 34:24.146
[sighs]

34:24.228 --> 34:25.522
I can't.

34:26.523 --> 34:28.442
I'm her mom.

34:28.525 --> 34:31.527
If she sees
how big my grief really is,

34:31.612 --> 34:33.197
it'll just scare her.

34:33.280 --> 34:35.699
♪ ♪

34:42.331 --> 34:45.375
I had a really bad episode
of depression a few years ago.

34:46.543 --> 34:48.545
And I felt like I was just...

34:48.629 --> 34:51.130
sitting at the bottom
of a deep hole,

34:51.215 --> 34:53.634
looking up at the world
going on above me.

34:54.676 --> 34:56.637
The friends that helped me
the most were not the ones

34:56.719 --> 34:58.388
who tried to get me out
of the hole.

34:59.431 --> 35:01.767
It was the friends
who climbed down into the hole,

35:01.850 --> 35:04.812
sat with me for a bit
that really made things better.

35:06.855 --> 35:08.232
I mean, there isn't a...

35:08.315 --> 35:10.651
right way to do this, Laurel.

35:13.904 --> 35:14.905
[chuckles softly]

35:14.988 --> 35:16.865
I should get back.

35:17.866 --> 35:19.743
I didn't see your name
on the author list.

35:19.827 --> 35:21.161
Are you here for your new book?

35:22.746 --> 35:25.958
Would it scare you off if
I told you I was here for you?

35:26.041 --> 35:28.627
Depends on where you take me
for dinner.

35:31.505 --> 35:32.965
I'll meet you back here at 7:00?

35:33.048 --> 35:34.842
Okay.

35:53.569 --> 35:55.571
♪ ♪

36:12.421 --> 36:14.965
[sighs]

36:15.048 --> 36:16.800
Okay, when I woke up
this morning,

36:16.884 --> 36:19.428
I did not expect to be here
doing this again.

36:19.511 --> 36:22.514
I used to love
the Great Boardwalk Showdown.

36:22.598 --> 36:24.933
Maybe I loved it
a little too much.

36:25.017 --> 36:27.853
All I cared about was if I won.

36:27.936 --> 36:30.230
But today is about us.

36:30.314 --> 36:32.900
Taylor, you've shown up for me
over and over again this year,

36:32.983 --> 36:35.068
and now I'm showing up for you.

36:36.069 --> 36:38.030
And, Skye, I know we just met

36:38.113 --> 36:40.365
and you probably think
we're all way too competitive,

36:40.449 --> 36:43.201
but our-our team wouldn't be
where we are without you.

36:43.285 --> 36:46.038
When Conrad chose
this team, he thought

36:46.121 --> 36:48.332
they had it in the bag.
But we have proven them wrong.

36:48.415 --> 36:53.045
And whether we win or lose, we
are worthy of that giant bag...

36:53.128 --> 36:55.464
Oh, you can be as inspirational
as you want, Belly.

36:55.547 --> 36:57.215
We're still going to kick
your asses.

36:57.299 --> 36:59.843
- Shut up, Steven.
- [overlapping chatter]

36:59.927 --> 37:01.345
All right.

37:02.721 --> 37:04.640
- I don't know about you guys...
- Ooh, I want this one.

37:04.723 --> 37:06.600
...but I feel the need...

37:06.683 --> 37:08.226
[all] The need for speed!

37:08.310 --> 37:09.561
Let's go!

37:09.645 --> 37:13.273
Drivers, start your engines!

37:13.357 --> 37:17.319
First team with all their cars
past the finish line wins.

37:17.402 --> 37:20.572
On your mark. Get set.

37:20.656 --> 37:22.324
[♪ Cake: "The Distance"]

37:22.407 --> 37:23.450
Go!

37:23.533 --> 37:25.577
- Go, go, go!
- [yelling]

37:25.661 --> 37:27.162
Floor it!

37:27.245 --> 37:28.956
You're going down!

37:29.039 --> 37:31.249
♪ Reckless and wild,
they pour through the turns ♪

37:31.333 --> 37:34.127
♪ Their prowess is potent
and secretly stern ♪

37:34.211 --> 37:35.879
♪ As they speed
through the finish ♪

37:35.963 --> 37:37.464
♪ The flags go down,
the fans get up...

37:37.547 --> 37:39.049
I'm coming for you, Belly!

37:39.132 --> 37:40.884
♪ The arena is empty
except for one man...

37:40.968 --> 37:43.053
You're going down, Taylor!

37:43.136 --> 37:44.304
♪ And striving
as fast as they can ♪

37:44.388 --> 37:46.181
Ooh!

37:46.264 --> 37:47.849
- Oh, I'm catching up.
- Oh! We're last!

37:47.933 --> 37:48.850
Catching up.
I'm catching up.

37:48.934 --> 37:51.103
We got this in the bag.

37:51.186 --> 37:52.688
♪ And hugging the turns ♪

37:52.771 --> 37:54.606
♪ And thinking of someone
for whom he still burns ♪

37:54.690 --> 37:56.358
Come on. Where is he?

37:56.441 --> 37:59.444
- ♪ He's going the distance ♪
- Oh, yeah!

37:59.528 --> 38:02.781
- ♪ He's going for speed ♪
- [whooping]

38:02.864 --> 38:04.491
- ♪ She's all alone ♪
- ♪ All alone! ♪

38:04.574 --> 38:06.785
♪ All alone in her time
of need ♪

38:06.868 --> 38:09.329
[Conrad] Oh, you're going down!

38:09.413 --> 38:10.956
Watch your back!

38:11.039 --> 38:12.791
Eat my fucking dust, bro!

38:12.874 --> 38:15.836
- I'm trying!
- Technically, you can merge
into the carpool lane.

38:15.919 --> 38:17.838
- The inside turn, right here!
- I got it, inside!

38:17.921 --> 38:19.297
Inside turn! Go, go, go, go!

38:19.381 --> 38:20.382
No, no. No, no, no, no!

38:20.465 --> 38:23.093
♪ ♪

38:23.176 --> 38:25.178
- Suck it!
- Fuck. Oh, no!

38:26.221 --> 38:27.723
- ♪ Yeah! ♪
- No!

38:28.974 --> 38:31.268
[distorted yelling]

38:31.351 --> 38:33.061
In your face! In your...

38:33.145 --> 38:34.396
Yeah!

38:34.479 --> 38:36.815
No! Oh, my God!

38:36.898 --> 38:39.359
- Oh, my God.
- [Skye groans]

38:39.443 --> 38:41.153
- Oh! Oh!
- That's my boy!

38:41.236 --> 38:42.654
That's my boy!

38:42.738 --> 38:45.157
♪ ♪

38:45.240 --> 38:47.743
Get ready to pay up, Belly.

38:47.826 --> 38:51.246
You know, I think that's why
our mom banned us from playing.

38:51.329 --> 38:52.581
I could pay. I mean,

38:52.664 --> 38:55.167
I made a ton of money
shorting bitcoin, so...

38:55.250 --> 38:56.626
You are one of the most
interesting people

38:56.710 --> 38:57.878
I've ever met.

39:01.423 --> 39:02.883
[sighs]

39:02.966 --> 39:04.926
- How you doing, Cinder-Belly?
- I mean, is it weird for me

39:05.010 --> 39:08.305
to be having an existential
crisis about this?

39:09.347 --> 39:11.266
Am I good enough
for our volleyball team

39:11.349 --> 39:14.478
if I can't even
win boardwalk games?

39:14.561 --> 39:16.146
No, we need you
on the team because

39:16.229 --> 39:17.814
you lost the boardwalk games.

39:17.898 --> 39:19.691
I mean, we have a great team,

39:19.775 --> 39:21.276
but that doesn't mean that
we're going to win every game.

39:21.359 --> 39:22.819
We need somebody that's
going to, like, lead us,

39:22.903 --> 39:24.654
