so you're good at this.

39:51.807 --> 39:53.725
You're a natural boss.

39:53.809 --> 39:56.103
[clears throat]
Sorry to interrupt.

39:56.186 --> 39:57.979
- Is it time?
- [Conrad] It is time.

39:58.063 --> 40:00.107
The Tower of Terror awaits.

40:00.190 --> 40:01.900
I'm gonna go get you a barf bag.

40:01.983 --> 40:05.028
Yeah, come on.

40:05.112 --> 40:07.447
[Skye] Let's go.

40:08.490 --> 40:11.201
Hey, no one said
you had to do this alone.

40:13.578 --> 40:16.123
I can keep you company
if you want me to.

40:17.457 --> 40:19.709
The key is just
to not think about it.

40:19.793 --> 40:21.211
Okay. Let's go.

40:21.294 --> 40:24.005
Come on. You got this.
You've done it before.

40:24.089 --> 40:25.966
[Belly] I know.

40:26.049 --> 40:28.218
♪ ♪

40:34.516 --> 40:36.476
[riders screaming]

40:39.729 --> 40:41.731
[indistinct chatter]

40:46.194 --> 40:48.238
All right.

40:48.321 --> 40:50.907
- It's now or never, I guess.
- Butterflies.

40:50.991 --> 40:53.118
- [Steven laughs]
- I guess so.

40:53.201 --> 40:54.911
- Come on!
- Come on!

40:54.995 --> 40:56.163
- Go, boss!
- Yes!

40:56.246 --> 40:57.330
- You got this!
- Come on, Jere.

40:57.414 --> 40:58.748
- [Taylor] Let's go!
- [whooping]

40:58.832 --> 41:00.125
- After you.
- [Conrad] Come on, Jere!

41:00.208 --> 41:03.753
[whooping, cheering continues]

41:03.837 --> 41:06.464
- [Taylor] You got this!
- [Conrad] You got this!

41:06.548 --> 41:08.717
Make sure you're really
buckled in, man.

41:08.800 --> 41:11.636
[♪ Guns N' Roses:
"Sweet Child O' Mine"]

41:17.058 --> 41:18.810
It's okay to be scared.

41:20.729 --> 41:22.814
ESP tell you that?

41:23.857 --> 41:25.317
No, your face did.

41:26.401 --> 41:30.155
Hey, don't worry.
I'm right here with you, okay?

41:32.449 --> 41:35.952
[Belly] Jeremiah is always
there when I need him.

41:36.036 --> 41:37.037
♪ That it seems to me...

41:37.120 --> 41:38.246
When I was 13,

41:38.330 --> 41:39.748
right before the Fourth of July,

41:39.831 --> 41:41.458
I caught a horrible summer cold.

41:41.541 --> 41:43.668
I hated being sick,
but the worst part

41:43.752 --> 41:45.712
about it was feeling
so left out.

41:45.795 --> 41:47.672
[Susannah] Ooh,
what are you up to, Jere-Bear?

41:47.756 --> 41:49.466
[Jeremiah] I was just going to
go to the boardwalk with Clay.

41:49.549 --> 41:51.426
[Susannah] Oh, yeah.
It's such a nice day.

41:51.509 --> 41:54.012
- [Jeremiah] Yeah.
- [Susannah] Poor Belly is
stuck inside with a cold.

41:54.095 --> 41:56.890
It'd be sweet of you
to keep her company.

41:56.973 --> 42:00.185
- Mom...
- Jere, please?

42:00.268 --> 42:02.687
[Jeremiah] I can go to
the boardwalk tomorrow.

42:02.771 --> 42:04.648
[Susannah] That's
my sunshine boy.

42:04.731 --> 42:07.025
[Belly] He stayed home with me
for the rest of the week.

42:07.108 --> 42:08.652
[laughing]

42:08.735 --> 42:10.070
And then when
he got sick two days later,

42:10.153 --> 42:12.280
I stayed home with him.

42:12.364 --> 42:14.741
♪ Whoa, oh-oh-oh,
sweet love of mine...

42:14.824 --> 42:16.743
[both laughing]

42:20.080 --> 42:23.833
♪ She's got eyes
of the bluest skies ♪

42:23.917 --> 42:27.504
♪ And if they thought of rain ♪

42:27.587 --> 42:31.424
♪ I'd hate to look
into those eyes ♪

42:31.508 --> 42:35.595
♪ And see an ounce of pain ♪

42:35.679 --> 42:36.596
♪ Whoa, oh-oh ♪

42:36.680 --> 42:37.597
[all screaming]

42:37.681 --> 42:39.891
♪ Sweet child o' mine ♪

42:42.644 --> 42:44.562
♪ Whoa, oh-oh-oh...

42:44.646 --> 42:47.107
- Oh!
- Oh, my God!

42:47.190 --> 42:48.817
[Taylor] Yes!

42:48.900 --> 42:51.736
- [Cam] Bravo, you guys!
- [Taylor whooping]

42:51.820 --> 42:54.948
[chatter continues]

42:55.031 --> 42:57.701
- Yeah! Yeah!
- All right, so what's next?

42:57.784 --> 43:00.787
- Yeah, dude. You did it.
- Interesting.

43:00.870 --> 43:03.206
- What?
- Nothing.

43:03.290 --> 43:05.250
It's just interesting.

43:06.376 --> 43:09.963
[indistinct chatter]

43:10.046 --> 43:12.048
Thanks for
looking out for us today.

43:12.132 --> 43:13.466
Yeah, no,
that was the least I could do.

43:13.550 --> 43:16.553
You guys, um, you guys
had a pretty tough year.

43:16.636 --> 43:17.762
Yeah. I don't know.

43:17.846 --> 43:20.807
It feels, like,
weird having some fun.

43:20.890 --> 43:23.268
Like, part of me feels guilty.

43:23.351 --> 43:25.478
I don't know
if that makes sense.

43:25.562 --> 43:27.939
Yeah, I know, I know
exactly what you mean.

43:28.023 --> 43:29.941
Yeah, I know you know.

43:32.610 --> 43:35.113
Today was really important
for you guys.

43:35.196 --> 43:37.532
Fun is important.
Very important.

43:40.327 --> 43:42.412
You want to come back
to the house with us?

43:42.495 --> 43:44.122
- I would love that.
- Cool.

43:44.205 --> 43:46.249
- Cool!
- [laughs]

43:46.333 --> 43:48.293
[♪ CamelPhat & Elderbrook:
"Cola"]

43:48.376 --> 43:50.128
♪ ♪

43:50.211 --> 43:52.547
- After you.
- Thank you.

43:52.630 --> 43:55.216
[Jeremiah] All aboard!

43:56.259 --> 43:58.762
♪ She's heading for the lights ♪

44:00.347 --> 44:02.766
♪ She sees the vision going ♪

44:04.184 --> 44:06.936
♪ Cutting out, left alive...

44:09.189 --> 44:10.440
I can't believe I'm saying this,

44:10.523 --> 44:12.859
but today was
actually really fun.

44:12.942 --> 44:14.402
Today was so much fun.

44:14.486 --> 44:16.363
Yeah.

44:16.446 --> 44:17.655
I don't know, man.

44:17.739 --> 44:19.616
I haven't seen you
this happy in a long time.

44:19.699 --> 44:22.118
♪ She can't tell
the difference yet...

44:22.202 --> 44:24.371
It felt good to feel
like a kid again.

44:24.454 --> 44:26.873
I'll tell you.

44:27.957 --> 44:31.378
And I know that my mom only
ever wanted us to be happy,

44:31.461 --> 44:33.463
